Sentencas: Composite electrolytes of lithium, sodium, and potassium carbonate ((LiNaK)(2)CO3), and samarium doped ceria (SDC) have been synthesized and the carbonate content optimized to study conductivity and its performance in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: High conductive (LiNaK)2CO3-Ce0.85Sm0.15O2 electrolyte compositions for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: Electrolyte compositions of 20, 25, 30, 35, 45 wt% (LiNaK)(2)CO3-SDC are fabricated and the physical and electrochemical characterization is carried out using X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy, electrochemical impedance spectroscope, and current-voltage measurements.
Titulo: High conductive (LiNaK)2CO3-Ce0.85Sm0.15O2 electrolyte compositions for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The ionic conductivity of (LiNaK)(2)CO3-SDC electrolytes increases with increasing carbonate content.
Titulo: High conductive (LiNaK)2CO3-Ce0.85Sm0.15O2 electrolyte compositions for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The best ionic conductivity is obtained for 45 wt% (LiNaK)(2)CO3-SDC composite electrolyte (0.72 S cm(-1) at 600 degrees C) followed by the 35 wt% (LiNaK)(2)CO3-SDC composite electrolyte (0.55 S cm(-1) at 600 degrees C).
Titulo: High conductive (LiNaK)2CO3-Ce0.85Sm0.15O2 electrolyte compositions for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The symmetrical cell of the 35 wt% (LiNaK)(2)CO3-SDC composite electrolyte with lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) electrode in air gives an area specific resistance of 0.155 Omega cm(2) at 500 degrees C.
Titulo: High conductive (LiNaK)2CO3-Ce0.85Sm0.15O2 electrolyte compositions for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the fuel cell using 35 wt% (LiNaK)(2)CO3-SDC composite electrolyte, composite NiO anode and composite LSCF cathode is found to be 801 mW cm(-2) at 550 degrees C. (C) 2017 Hydrogen Energy Publications LLC.
Titulo: High conductive (LiNaK)2CO3-Ce0.85Sm0.15O2 electrolyte compositions for IT-SOFC applications
